@node Usage "SmartTrash - Usage"
@smartwrap


@{b}Usage

=====@{ub}


  To start SmartTrash, double click on the icon, or drag it to the WBStartup
drawer of your boot disk to have it start automatically.


  SmartTrash puts an appicon on your workbench.


  Double click on the icon - to get a requester allowing you to quit the
program.


  Drag one or more files or drawer over the icon - SmartTrash will move them
to a trashcan drawer in the root directory.  If there is already a file with
the same name, SmartTrash will rename the new file "Copy_of_<filename>" or
"Copy_2_of<filename>".  If there is a problem (i.e. file in use, file
protected from deletion etc...), SmartTrash will restore the file and its
icon.


  By default, SmartTrash tries to move the files into a drawer named
@{b}Trashcan@{ub} in the root of the disk.  If that fails, it will try @{b}T@{ub}.
If both fail, it will try to create a directory and icon, named Trashcan,
then T.  If both fail, no action will be taken.


  Drag a disk or an appicon onto the SmartTrash appicon - SmartTrash will
ignore it.


  SmartTrash can add a menu item to the tool menu instead of / in addition
to the appicon (set it through tooltypes).  This works EXACTLY the same as
the AppIcon.

@endnode

@node Configuration "SmartTrash - Configuration"
@wordwrap

@{b}Configuration
=============@{ub}


  SmartTrash is configured using TOOLTYPES, which are grouped into three classes.

  @{"  AppIcon   " link Configuration.AppIcon}
  @{"  AppMenu   " link Configuration.AppMenu}
  @{" TrashPath  " link Configuration.TrashPath}

@endnode

@node Configuration.AppIcon "SmartTrash - Configuration - AppIcon"
@smartwrap


@{b}AppIcon

=======@{ub}


  The AppIcon is cloned from the SmartTrash icon, has the same name, and is
put in the first convenient spot.


  SmartTrash supports the following tooltypes to control the appicon


      LEFTEDGE=<nnn>                   e.g. LEFTEDGE=550

      TOPEDGE =<nnn>                   e.g. TOPEDGE =195

      ICONNAME=<legend>                e.g. ICONNAME=WasteBasket

      ICONFILE=<filename>              e.g. ICONFILE=SYS:Trashcan


  Note that the iconfile does not require a ".info" extension.

  If the iconfile does not specify a file/drawer with an icon, the default
Trashcan icon will be used instead.

@endnode

@node Configuration.AppMenu "SmartTrash - Configuration - AppMenuItem"
@smartwrap


@{b}AppMenuItem

===========@{ub}


  By default, SmartTrash only creates an appicon.  If you want SmartTrash
to create a TOOLS menu item, set the menu name.


      MENUITEM=<item>                  e.g. MENUITEM=Move to root

      MENUONLY=<bool>                  e.g. MENUONLY=TRUE


  The MenuOnly option forces SmartTrash to only use a menu item.  The Menu
item must be set for this option to work (or you'd have no way to use it!)

@endnode

@node Configuration.TrashPath "SmartTrash - Configuration - TrashPath"
@smartwrap


@{b}TrashPath

=========@{ub}


  By default, SmartTrash will move files to :Trashcan, falling back on :T.
The path may contain any number of directories, seperated by ';', though
the total path must be less than 128 bytes (currently).  Each component
MUST begin with a ':', and should not end in a '/'.  There is no checking
in this release.


      TRASHPATH=<trash path>           e.g. TRASHPATH=:Trashcan;:T

@endnode

@node Bugs "SmartTrash - Bugs"
@smartwrap


@{b}Bugs

====@{ub}


  If you drag a file from the trashcan onto the appicon, it will be renamed.
I guess it should either not touch it, or actually delete it.


  BUGGETTE: if you drag a drawer icon which doesnt have a drawer attached to
it onto the appicon, it will cause SmartTrash to open its ABOUT window.
This is a "feature" of AppIcons, not a bug in my program.  Try it out on
other AppIcons.


  BUGGETTE: if you drag an iconless file (using SHOW->ALL FILES) to the
appicon, it will not appear in the trashcan window if it is currently open,
even if that has SHOW->ALL FILES selected.  Why?  Icons are written to disk
with PutDiskObject.  This also notifies workbench to update its icon, if it
would be visible.  If the file doesnt have an icon, SmartTrash doesnt call
PutDiskObject, and so Workbench doensnt realise anything has changed.


  There are no other known bugs, although as I dont have access to an MMU
equipped machine, I dont know if you will get enforcer hits.

@endnode

@node Future "SmartTrash - Future"
@smartwrap


@{b}Future

======@{ub}


  Heres a brief list of things I've considered, but not yet implemented.


  ░ Better error reporting, such as IF and WHY something failed.

  ░ The option to automatically unprotect a file from deletion, so that it
can be moved.

  ░ Send a command to a REXX Port (to use UPD).

  ░ Option to format a disk if thats dropped onto it.

  ░ Option to DELETE a file if it is currently in the trashcan.

  ░ Turning it into a commodity, so that only one is running at any time.

  ░ Options to set whether it creates a trashcan drawer automatically, not
at all, or ask the user.

  ░ Validation of tooltypes, especially the TRASHDIR.

  ░ Improve the About window, so that you can continue to drop icons onto
the appicon when its open.


  What I'd really like, though, is for the new Workbench engineers to make
SmartTrash completely obsolete, by making a new virtual Trashcan.  This
would behave just like SmartTrash, but when you double click on it, it
behaves like a drawer, and opens up a window, which contains the combined
contents of all the trashcan directories of all the mounted drives.

@endnode

